cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "XXL Lysimeter Experiment — Fürth 2022 dataset"
message: "If you use this dataset, please cite it as below."
type: dataset
authors:
  - name: "Carbon Drawdown Initiative (Carbdown GmbH)"
    website: "https://www.carbon-drawdown.de"
    city: "Fürth"
    country: DE
  - family-names: "Paessler"
    given-names: "Dirk"
    email: "dirk@dirkpaessler.com"
    affiliation: "Carbon Drawdown Initiative"
abstract: >-
  Data, code and figures from the Carbon Drawdown Initiative XXL Lysimeter enhanced-
  weathering experiment on soil "Fürth 2022": twenty outdoor lysimeter pots (0.406 m²
  each), control plus basalt at 100/200/400 t/ha and a fine grind, sampled ~monthly
  2022–2026 for leachate total alkalinity (CO₂-drawdown proxy), major ions, pH and EC,
  with buried soil sensors (moisture, temperature, EC, pH, CO₂), on-site and official
  weather, and feedstock characterization. Companion to the two-year greenhouse study.
keywords:
  - "enhanced weathering"
  - "enhanced rock weathering"
  - "carbon dioxide removal"
  - "total alkalinity"
  - "MRV"
  - "lysimeter"
  - "soil sensors"
version: "1.0"
date-released: "2026-07-04"
license: CC-BY-4.0
url: "https://www.carbon-drawdown.de"
